  <description type="morphology">Plants glabrous, glaucous. Stems 20–100 cm. Leaf blades 2–10 cm, base cuneate to cordate. Cymes open, 16–50(–100)-flowered. Pedicels (5–)10–30(–55) mm. Flowers: calyx 9–17 mm, with 5 prominent, usually green, winged angles or ridges, each ridge with strong, cordlike marginal vein; petals with claw 8–14 mm, blade 3–8 mm. Capsules included in calyx tube. Seeds 2–2.5 mm wide. 2n = 30.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering spring-summer.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Fields, waste places;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0-2400 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">introduced; Alta., B.C., Man., N.B., N.S., Ont., Que., Sask., Yukon; Ala., Alaska, Ariz., Ark., Calif., Colo., Conn., Del., D.C., Fla., Idaho, Ill., Ind., Iowa, Kans., Ky., La., Maine, Md., Mass., Mich., Minn., Miss., Mo., Mont., Nebr., Nev., N.H., N.J., N.Mex., N.Y., N.Dak., Ohio, Okla., Oreg., Pa., R.I., S.C., S.Dak., Tenn., Tex., Utah, Vt., Va., Wash., W.Va., Wis., Wyo.; Eurasia; widely naturalized elsewhere.</description>
